The paper deals with fine-grained image recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves attention-based learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new dataset, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
